1
00:00:22,464 --> 00:00:26,432
♪Should we forget yesterday's sorrows♪

2
00:00:26,432 --> 00:00:29,728
♪And the dazed confusion♪

3
00:00:30,976 --> 00:00:33,681
♪Should we let go of♪

4
00:00:33,681 --> 00:00:35,904
♪The stubborn madness♪

5
00:00:35,904 --> 00:00:39,072
♪And naive recklessness now♪

6
00:00:40,192 --> 00:00:43,840
♪Those years, those faces♪

7
00:00:44,992 --> 00:00:48,763
♪Those old scars we can't erase♪

8
00:00:49,824 --> 00:00:52,460
♪Tears streaming, facing the light♪

9
00:00:53,152 --> 00:00:57,594
♪Piercing the sorrow within♪

10
00:01:08,716 --> 00:01:12,736
♪The road ahead's long,
stumbling all the way♪

11
00:01:13,536 --> 00:01:18,076
♪The wounds we've borne
are medals hidden within♪

12
00:01:18,336 --> 00:01:22,391
♪Standing alone on an open plain♪

13
00:01:23,168 --> 00:01:26,851
♪We gaze at the stars♪

14
00:01:31,228 --> 00:01:34,816
=The Dream Maker=

15
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,848
=Episode 34=

16
00:01:54,744 --> 00:01:55,264
Sun Xiaoyan.

17
00:01:57,624 --> 00:01:58,303
Mr. Xie.

18
00:01:58,984 --> 00:01:59,824
(Shop for Lease)
Why are you here?

19
00:02:00,664 --> 00:02:01,824
I'm looking for a place.

20
00:02:03,223 --> 00:02:04,664
For the karaoke bar, right?

21
00:02:05,984 --> 00:02:06,544
Right here?

22
00:02:06,583 --> 00:02:07,223
Yes.

23
00:02:10,504 --> 00:02:11,303
No wonder

24
00:02:11,544 --> 00:02:13,664
it's been so long with no news.

25
00:02:14,504 --> 00:02:15,743
Haven't even rented a place?

26
00:02:16,664 --> 00:02:17,623
I'm looking for it.

27
00:02:27,384 --> 00:02:28,224
This place is good.

28
00:02:30,344 --> 00:02:31,183
This is nice.

29
00:02:33,104 --> 00:02:33,863
Good location.

30
00:02:34,544 --> 00:02:35,224
Not cheap, is it?

31
00:02:35,664 --> 00:02:36,583
No, it's not cheap.

32
00:02:37,703 --> 00:02:39,863
So, did you get it?

33
00:02:41,863 --> 00:02:42,463
Not yet.

34
00:02:45,743 --> 00:02:46,903
Tell me if you have trouble.

35
00:02:47,903 --> 00:02:48,944
It's up to you.

36
00:02:50,544 --> 00:02:51,463
Is it about money?

37
00:02:54,344 --> 00:02:55,504
The landlord insists

38
00:02:55,984 --> 00:02:58,183
I pay a full year's rent upfront,

39
00:02:58,303 --> 00:02:59,583
or he'll rent it to others.

40
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:01,064
I've asked for a loan.

41
00:03:01,064 --> 00:03:04,224
However, I'm currently
unable to obtain the loan.

42
00:03:04,863 --> 00:03:05,903
I'm trying to find a way.

43
00:03:07,423 --> 00:03:08,224
This place is good.

44
00:03:09,368 --> 00:03:10,296
How much do you need?

45
00:03:10,984 --> 00:03:11,423
30,000.

46
00:03:11,784 --> 00:03:12,224
30,000.

47
00:03:13,784 --> 00:03:14,463
Not too much.

48
00:03:15,032 --> 00:03:15,903
I'll lend it to you.

49
00:03:16,863 --> 00:03:19,903
Pay me back with the same interest rate
as the credit union, okay?

50
00:03:21,104 --> 00:03:22,183
Mr. Xie, well...

51
00:03:22,264 --> 00:03:23,064
This is no big deal.

52
00:03:23,623 --> 00:03:24,344
You wait here.

53
00:03:25,303 --> 00:03:26,064
I'll get the money.

54
00:03:26,784 --> 00:03:28,863
I-I'll pay you back
as soon as I get the loan.

55
00:03:29,224 --> 00:03:29,784
No problem.

56
00:03:30,544 --> 00:03:31,703
Thank you, Mr. Xie.

57
00:03:32,104 --> 00:03:33,544
I'm glad to help people of Yuehai.

58
00:03:33,863 --> 00:03:34,824
Go keep an eye on it.

59
00:03:41,183 --> 00:03:41,544
Here.

60
00:03:42,544 --> 00:03:43,224
What's this?

61
00:03:43,384 --> 00:03:45,984
I originally wanted to show a movie
for Grandma in the square.

62
00:03:46,264 --> 00:03:48,504
Ms. Li said I should let everyone know.

63
00:03:48,743 --> 00:03:50,463
Anyone interested is welcome to watch.

64
00:03:50,903 --> 00:03:51,664
What movie?

65
00:03:52,463 --> 00:03:54,384
It says on it. Crossroads.

66
00:03:56,463 --> 00:03:57,504
What kind of movie is it?

67
00:03:57,944 --> 00:03:59,064
The newest kung fu movie?

68
00:03:59,303 --> 00:03:59,824
No.

69
00:03:59,984 --> 00:04:01,664
It's just an old black-and-white movie.

70
00:04:02,583 --> 00:04:03,463
An old movie?

71
00:04:03,463 --> 00:04:06,474
(Broadcast Room)

72
00:04:06,504 --> 00:04:07,064
Xiaohai.

73
00:04:07,824 --> 00:04:09,743
You've watched the world.

74
00:04:09,903 --> 00:04:11,264
Why are you getting old-fashioned?

75
00:04:12,703 --> 00:04:14,944
Now, everyone has a color TV set.

76
00:04:15,264 --> 00:04:16,584
The TV shows are all good.

77
00:04:17,176 --> 00:04:18,680
Who will watch black-and-white films?

78
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:20,024
Yes, I know.

79
00:04:20,183 --> 00:04:22,784
But this old copy is all I could get.

80
00:04:23,584 --> 00:04:24,224
Besides,

81
00:04:24,544 --> 00:04:26,183
how small a TV screen is.

82
00:04:26,503 --> 00:04:27,623
Movies are awesome.

83
00:04:27,823 --> 00:04:29,823
That giant screen, right?

84
00:04:30,144 --> 00:04:30,784
True.

85
00:04:30,984 --> 00:04:31,664
Go play it.

86
00:04:32,104 --> 00:04:33,263
Okay, I'll do it.

87
00:04:34,296 --> 00:04:35,544
Don't blame me if nobody comes.

88
00:04:35,704 --> 00:04:36,303
No, I won't.

89
00:04:36,823 --> 00:04:37,623
Thanks a lot.

90
00:04:37,863 --> 00:04:38,544
No problem.

91
00:04:40,024 --> 00:04:41,664
Attention. I'm broadcasting a notice.

92
00:04:57,263 --> 00:04:57,904
Qingtian.

93
00:05:00,823 --> 00:05:02,024
Why are you so late?

94
00:05:02,183 --> 00:05:02,863
Come on.

95
00:05:03,024 --> 00:05:03,704
You scared me!

96
00:05:03,904 --> 00:05:04,423
What's wrong?

97
00:05:04,704 --> 00:05:05,943
Didn't you hear the broadcast?

98
00:05:07,024 --> 00:05:07,464
No.

99
00:05:08,464 --> 00:05:09,303
Tonight,

100
00:05:09,904 --> 00:05:11,704
Yang Xiaohai is showing a movie
in the square.

101
00:05:12,464 --> 00:05:13,383
Let's go watch.

102
00:05:13,823 --> 00:05:14,383
You scared me.

103
00:05:14,464 --> 00:05:15,584
Can't you be a bit steadier?

104
00:05:16,423 --> 00:05:16,943
Let's go.

105
00:05:20,784 --> 00:05:21,183
Let's go.

106
00:05:21,784 --> 00:05:22,383
Wait.

107
00:05:22,712 --> 00:05:23,503
Why did you get on?

108
00:05:23,784 --> 00:05:24,503
Your own bike?

109
00:05:25,383 --> 00:05:26,623
M-My bike's broken.

110
00:05:27,024 --> 00:05:28,784
Can't you just give me a ride?

111
00:05:29,984 --> 00:05:32,584
Fine. Give me that.

112
00:05:38,423 --> 00:05:39,823
Hold on tight.

113
00:05:44,863 --> 00:05:45,623
Hold on tight.

114
00:05:48,544 --> 00:05:49,904
What are you doing?

115
00:05:50,144 --> 00:05:51,344
My dad's sleeping.

116
00:06:15,623 --> 00:06:16,383
She didn't come?

117
00:06:20,863 --> 00:06:22,144
Stuff was delivered,

118
00:06:22,904 --> 00:06:23,704
yet she didn't come.

119
00:06:23,984 --> 00:06:24,503
Granny,

120
00:06:24,704 --> 00:06:25,743
be quiet.

121
00:06:27,063 --> 00:06:27,664
Focus.

122
00:06:36,183 --> 00:06:37,104
What's wrong?

123
00:06:37,784 --> 00:06:38,784
Hai, what's wrong?

124
00:06:39,823 --> 00:06:40,823
Why's there no sound?

125
00:06:45,464 --> 00:06:46,383
Sorry about that.

126
00:06:46,823 --> 00:06:49,063
I think this copy is too old.

127
00:06:49,664 --> 00:06:52,024
Let me swap it for a new movie.

128
00:06:52,423 --> 00:06:54,503
No! We want to watch this one.

129
00:06:54,704 --> 00:06:56,183
Yes, we insist on this.

130
00:06:56,344 --> 00:06:57,823
But this movie suddenly has no sound.

131
00:06:58,144 --> 00:06:58,704
Xiaohai.

132
00:06:59,743 --> 00:07:00,183
What is it?

133
00:07:02,904 --> 00:07:06,328
The copy's too old. No sound.

134
00:07:06,328 --> 00:07:07,096
I'm changing it.

135
00:07:07,263 --> 00:07:09,063
If they want it, let them watch.

136
00:07:09,544 --> 00:07:10,743
Everyone, stay calm.

137
00:07:11,263 --> 00:07:13,664
We'll watch this movie tonight.

138
00:07:13,904 --> 00:07:16,224
He and I
will dub it live together, okay?

139
00:07:16,664 --> 00:07:17,743
Can you do it?

140
00:07:17,904 --> 00:07:18,984
No problem. I got this.

141
00:07:21,144 --> 00:07:21,984
Be careful!

142
00:07:23,024 --> 00:07:23,784
I'm fine.

143
00:07:28,503 --> 00:07:29,024
Let's do it.

144
00:07:32,743 --> 00:07:33,344
Granny.

145
00:07:36,623 --> 00:07:37,263
Sit.

146
00:07:41,784 --> 00:07:43,464
Eyes forward, everyone.

147
00:07:46,104 --> 00:07:47,144
Really beautiful.

148
00:07:47,144 --> 00:07:47,784
Really?

149
00:07:49,624 --> 00:07:55,104
Now, this lady, Wang Lili,
and I will dub the movie together.

150
00:07:55,423 --> 00:07:56,664
We'll do the voices.

151
00:07:56,664 --> 00:07:57,503
- Great!
- Great!

152
00:08:03,743 --> 00:08:05,104
Oh, it's her!

153
00:08:05,303 --> 00:08:05,784
Good...

154
00:08:07,144 --> 00:08:08,024
Good eye.

155
00:08:08,344 --> 00:08:08,943
Granny.

156
00:08:09,224 --> 00:08:10,263
We're starting the dub.

157
00:08:10,464 --> 00:08:11,383
Be quiet.

158
00:08:11,863 --> 00:08:12,623
Look at me.

159
00:08:15,544 --> 00:08:16,024
Lili.

160
00:08:16,544 --> 00:08:18,183
Want me to explain this scene?

161
00:08:18,383 --> 00:08:19,704
I'll follow your lead.

162
00:08:19,784 --> 00:08:21,144
I can catch up.

163
00:08:23,423 --> 00:08:24,344
Let's begin.

164
00:08:29,263 --> 00:08:30,503
Why isn't she here yet?

165
00:08:32,783 --> 00:08:34,023
What's wrong?

166
00:08:37,464 --> 00:08:38,143
I...

167
00:08:40,623 --> 00:08:43,263
I saw a beautiful fish in the river.

168
00:08:44,064 --> 00:08:45,383
Beautiful fish?

169
00:08:46,143 --> 00:08:47,143
Where?

170
00:08:50,104 --> 00:08:52,023
You should say, "I'm late."

171
00:08:53,424 --> 00:08:54,263
I'm late.

172
00:08:55,023 --> 00:08:57,143
You're soaked!

173
00:08:59,383 --> 00:09:01,304
He was scared you wouldn't come.

174
00:09:01,304 --> 00:09:01,984
Granny.

175
00:09:03,543 --> 00:09:04,663
Eat this.

176
00:09:04,984 --> 00:09:05,783
Quiet now.

177
00:09:07,143 --> 00:09:07,783
Not at all.

178
00:09:08,143 --> 00:09:09,503
I arrived too early.

179
00:09:11,944 --> 00:09:13,623
This is the gift you gave me.

180
00:09:14,224 --> 00:09:16,503
Do I look pretty in it?

181
00:09:17,783 --> 00:09:19,064
Y-Yes.

182
00:09:19,783 --> 00:09:21,584
I sent you so many postcards.

183
00:09:21,903 --> 00:09:23,143
You never replied.

184
00:09:24,424 --> 00:09:25,503
How could I?

185
00:09:26,023 --> 00:09:27,824
You were always on the move.

186
00:09:28,263 --> 00:09:31,023
Never staying in one spot.

187
00:09:32,623 --> 00:09:33,663
This liquor smells great.

188
00:09:33,863 --> 00:09:35,023
- Sure.
- Sure.

189
00:09:35,143 --> 00:09:36,263
Good drinker.

190
00:09:36,783 --> 00:09:37,543
Crabs are ready!

191
00:09:37,543 --> 00:09:38,263
Sit.

192
00:09:38,623 --> 00:09:39,743
Ms. Gao, all dishes served.

193
00:09:40,064 --> 00:09:41,304
Enjoy yourselves!

194
00:09:41,543 --> 00:09:42,543
- Great.
- Great.

195
00:09:43,543 --> 00:09:45,224
Ms. Gao, your assistant is impressive.

196
00:09:45,383 --> 00:09:46,224
Good work ability.

197
00:09:46,424 --> 00:09:47,304
Good drinker.

198
00:09:47,824 --> 00:09:48,743
Of course.

199
00:09:48,824 --> 00:09:49,663
My new assistant.

200
00:09:49,863 --> 00:09:50,704
Her name's Jessica.

201
00:09:51,064 --> 00:09:52,543
She studied abroad.

202
00:09:52,863 --> 00:09:54,143
Sir, two seafood noodles.

203
00:09:54,304 --> 00:09:54,903
Okay!

204
00:09:56,383 --> 00:09:58,663
Come on! Let's try the food.

205
00:09:59,224 --> 00:10:00,263
For seafood,

206
00:10:00,344 --> 00:10:02,623
skip fancy restaurants in Yuehai.

207
00:10:03,064 --> 00:10:04,543
Come to street stalls like this.

208
00:10:04,824 --> 00:10:05,663
Amazing flavor.

209
00:10:05,783 --> 00:10:07,143
Try it! Go on.

210
00:10:07,304 --> 00:10:10,263
I passed Yan's wonton stall earlier

211
00:10:10,424 --> 00:10:11,304
and wanted a bowl.

212
00:10:11,623 --> 00:10:12,944
But I found her stall was closed.

213
00:10:14,064 --> 00:10:15,143
Didn't you know?

214
00:10:15,584 --> 00:10:17,184
Sun Xiaoyan has landed on her feet.

215
00:10:17,663 --> 00:10:18,944
She doesn't care about a stall.

216
00:10:20,663 --> 00:10:21,023
Why?

217
00:10:21,023 --> 00:10:21,704
Listen,

218
00:10:22,143 --> 00:10:24,503
she and Mr. Xie are an item.

219
00:10:26,224 --> 00:10:27,023
Is that true?

220
00:10:27,503 --> 00:10:29,184
I saw it with my own eyes the other day.

221
00:10:29,543 --> 00:10:31,543
They came out of a shop together,

222
00:10:31,824 --> 00:10:33,663
laughing and chatting. Quite close.

223
00:10:35,064 --> 00:10:35,623
No, sit.

224
00:10:36,104 --> 00:10:36,984
Don't worry about it.

225
00:10:37,383 --> 00:10:39,184
I know exactly
what kind of person Xie is.

226
00:10:39,263 --> 00:10:40,304
Take care of our guests.

227
00:10:41,304 --> 00:10:44,704
No wonder
Mr. Xie's been staying in the dorm.

228
00:10:44,743 --> 00:10:45,984
Come on. Keep eating!

229
00:10:45,984 --> 00:10:46,383
Well...

230
00:10:46,984 --> 00:10:47,304
Try it.

231
00:10:47,304 --> 00:10:49,224
Has he divorced Gao Xuemei yet?

232
00:10:50,143 --> 00:10:50,623
No idea.

233
00:10:51,064 --> 00:10:51,903
But having said that,

234
00:10:52,584 --> 00:10:55,743
no man could handle a woman
like Gao Xuemei.

235
00:10:56,584 --> 00:10:59,143
Of course,
men prefer young and pretty women

236
00:10:59,143 --> 00:11:01,584
like Sun Xiaoyan.

237
00:11:01,903 --> 00:11:02,344
Oh, please.

238
00:11:03,584 --> 00:11:04,304
I'm serious.

239
00:11:06,143 --> 00:11:08,704
Did you know
Sun Xiaoyan is opening a karaoke bar?

240
00:11:09,023 --> 00:11:09,663
Sure.

241
00:11:10,023 --> 00:11:12,903
Right by the traffic light
on Xincheng Road.

242
00:11:13,424 --> 00:11:15,984
Mr. Xie put up the money for her bar.

243
00:11:16,383 --> 00:11:17,663
I saw it myself.

244
00:11:18,344 --> 00:11:19,543
In a kraft paper bag,

245
00:11:19,743 --> 00:11:20,663
this big!

246
00:11:23,464 --> 00:11:24,543
- Ms. Gao!
- Ms. Gao!

247
00:11:24,704 --> 00:11:25,184
Ms. Gao?

248
00:11:25,184 --> 00:11:26,064
It's fine.

249
00:11:30,663 --> 00:11:32,344
Is she going to catch them cheating?

250
00:11:32,344 --> 00:11:33,143
This should be good.

251
00:11:33,344 --> 00:11:34,143
Let's go see.

252
00:11:35,623 --> 00:11:36,383
Keep the change!

253
00:11:36,383 --> 00:11:37,263
Told you to be quiet.

254
00:11:37,263 --> 00:11:38,064
You started it.

255
00:11:38,984 --> 00:11:39,903
Mr. Xie.

256
00:11:43,424 --> 00:11:44,863
Sun Xiaoyan moved her stall here?

257
00:11:45,064 --> 00:11:46,143
Yes, Mr. Xie.

258
00:11:46,424 --> 00:11:48,663
Yan is opening her karaoke bar here,

259
00:11:48,863 --> 00:11:50,584
so she moved the stall right here.

260
00:11:51,623 --> 00:11:52,743
That's a smart idea!

261
00:11:53,224 --> 00:11:54,263
She has it both ways.

262
00:11:54,543 --> 00:11:55,903
(Yan Dance Hall)
Yes, that's right.

263
00:11:56,863 --> 00:11:58,143
After singing,

264
00:11:58,304 --> 00:11:59,304
customers can eat here.

265
00:11:59,903 --> 00:12:00,464
Mr. Xie,

266
00:12:00,584 --> 00:12:01,663
let me get you wontons.

267
00:12:01,824 --> 00:12:04,064
Not now. I'll definitely come later.

268
00:12:05,783 --> 00:12:06,424
I already paid.

269
00:12:06,808 --> 00:12:08,543
(Construction Site. Keep Out)

270
00:12:08,543 --> 00:12:10,704
Yan Dance Hall.

271
00:12:12,543 --> 00:12:13,663
Working fast.

272
00:12:14,143 --> 00:12:15,543
The entrance is already decorated.

273
00:12:15,623 --> 00:12:17,863
Yes, still working on the inside.

274
00:12:18,168 --> 00:12:19,064
Where's Sun Xiaoyan?

275
00:12:19,584 --> 00:12:20,263
She is away.

276
00:12:20,263 --> 00:12:21,224
She'll be back soon.

277
00:12:23,304 --> 00:12:24,824
Too many things to do.

278
00:12:49,184 --> 00:12:49,944
Electrician?

279
00:12:50,424 --> 00:12:51,184
That's me.

280
00:12:51,824 --> 00:12:52,344
What's up?

281
00:12:55,320 --> 00:12:57,368
You started painting
before the wiring was done?

282
00:12:58,464 --> 00:13:00,184
The owner is away,
so you're slacking off?

283
00:13:00,944 --> 00:13:02,143
The wiring's all laid out.

284
00:13:03,383 --> 00:13:04,464
Why are you working alone?

285
00:13:05,424 --> 00:13:06,944
She can't afford many people.

286
00:13:07,623 --> 00:13:08,503
I can do it all.

287
00:13:09,304 --> 00:13:09,912
I'm a good man,

288
00:13:10,464 --> 00:13:11,464
so I undertake it all.

289
00:13:12,023 --> 00:13:12,623
Impressive.

290
00:13:12,984 --> 00:13:14,344
Yuehai has skilled people.

291
00:13:15,224 --> 00:13:16,984
Your paint job doesn't look great.

292
00:13:20,383 --> 00:13:21,263
Mr. Xie,

293
00:13:21,743 --> 00:13:23,184
